<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-32-0533 </DOCNO><TEXT>The size of financial support for the West German coal industry has becomeevident due to the weak dollar, the crash in oil prices, the steel industrycrisis and a stagnant electricity growth rate. The coal industry arguesthat the federal economy ministry's suggested cuts would result in atleast 40,000 job losses in the industry itself and related industries.The article outlines the arguments currently taking place concerningchoice of fuel and financing for the electricity industry. The decliningsteel industry has also meant a fall in domestic coal and coke sales,but the article suggests that the full impact cannot yet be calculated.9 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>